screening of tony & talk by a survivor of the conflict in uganda events at stanford screening of tony & talk by a survivor of the conflict in uganda facebook twitter email print add to calendar come watch invisible children's latest documentary tony and meet a survivor of africa's longest running war invisible children is a non profit that works to transform apathy into activism by documenting the lives of those living in regions of conflict and injustice they hope to educate and inspire individuals in the western world to use their unique voice for change their media creates an opportunity for people to become part of a grassroots movement that intelligently responds to what's happening in the world but their work extends beyond our nation's borders in war affected regions they focus on long term development working directly with individuals and institutions that are eager to realize their full potential through education and innovative economic opportunities they partner with affected communities and strive to improve the quality of life for individuals living in conflict and post conflict regions when thursday november 10 2011 8 00 pm approximate duration of 1.0 hour s where branner dining hall map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags humanities public service other international sponsor the branner hall public service focus contact friedler stanford edu admission free & open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 296 29697 last modified november 7 2011
